    "en": {
      "title": "24 hours approval for investors - ministerial notification",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Investment Promotion Minister Dammika Perera said that arrangements are being made to issue permits within 24 hours to international investors who want to make investments in Sri Lanka.",
        "He said the above while commenting to Veerakesari about the next steps to overcome the economic crisis of the country.",
        "I am carrying out my activities with dedication to overcome the current economic crisis. Discussions have been started to attract investors to the country.",
        "For this, negotiations are being carried out with diplomatic and other professional international parties.",
        "In particular, we have decided to extend the visa period for owners and employees of foreign companies in Sri Lanka to 5 years at a time.",
        "The activities for that have been officially started from last Friday. In the next step, the one-day service for obtaining passports will be started in the outer districts from tomorrow, Monday.",
        "In this situation, steps have been taken to grant permission of the Board of Investment within 24 hours to international investors who are proposing to make investments in Sri Lanka.",
        "It has been decided to speed up the process as it has been pointed out to me that there are delays in obtaining approvals for investments in Sri Lanka.",
        "And, specifically, measures have been taken to ensure that revenues are raised and spent in a fair, responsible and efficient manner to support Sri Lanka's social and economic investment priorities."
      ],
